<p>Reports missing continuation characters in <code>RUN</code> command.</p>
<p>
  In the <i>shell</i> form of <code>RUN</code> command you should use a '\' (backslash)
  to continue a single <code>RUN</code> instruction onto the next line.
  Otherwise, Docker build will fail.
</p>
<!-- tooltip end -->
<p><b>Examples:</b></p>
<pre><code>
  # the command below will fail
  RUN /bin/bash -c 'source $HOME/.bashrc;
      echo $HOME'
</code></pre>
<p>After the quick-fix is applied:</p>
<pre><code>
  RUN /bin/bash -c 'source $HOME/.bashrc; \
      echo $HOME'
</code></pre>
</body>
